				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Regen hitting Monks?????<a name="36219"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 23 04 4:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, just to make sure there aren't any misconceptions...
<br />

<br />
Let's start with the simplest situation, monk fd's out of song range with agro mobs.  His fd works and he doesn't get the &quot;fallen to the ground&quot; failure message and his fd isn't broken by a casting mob finishing casting on him.  After the mobs wander off you can move up so he's in song range, the cleric can come up and heal him, the necro can come up and try to sacrifice him as a joke...doesn't matter, agro will not be passed.  The monk may still be on some mobs agro list, but as long as you don't cast on him, sing at him, after he stands up, agro will not be passed.
<br />

<br />
Second situation, fd fails or is broken by a casting mob.  Any song or spell that lands on the monk will pass agro and train the group.  Monk says something witty, like, &quot;crap.&quot;
<br />

<br />
Third situation, song or pc spell hits monk before he fd's, agro is passed.  Everyone says something witty.
<br />

<br />
Formerly Ranador Kuroneko, 64th Monk, now...</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
